        <custom_item>
          type            : AUDIT_EXCHANGE
          description     : "EX13-EG-000200 - Exchange Attachment filtering must remove undesirable attachments by file type."
          info            : "By performing filtering at the perimeter, up to 90 percent of spam, malware, and other undesirable messages are eliminated from the message stream rather than admitting them into the mail server environment.

Attachments are being used more frequently for different forms of attacks. By filtering undesirable attachments a large percent of malicious code can be prevented from entering the system. Attachments must be controlled at the entry point into the email environment to prevent successful attachment-based attacks. The following is a basic list of known attachments that should be filtered from Internet mail attachments:

*.ade  *.crt  *.jse  *.msi  *.scr  *.wsh  *.dir
*.adp  *.csh  *.ksh  *.msp  *.sct  *.htm  *.dcr
*.app  *.exe  *.lnk  *.mst  *.shb  *.html  *.plg
*.asx  *.fxp  *.mda  *.ops  *.shs  *.htc  *.spl
*.bas  *.hlp  *.mdb  *.pcd  *.url  *.mht  *.swf
*.bat  *.hta  *.mde  *.pif  *.vb  *.mhtml  *.zip
*.chm  *.inf  *.mdt  *.prf  *.vbe  *.shtm
*.cmd  *.ins  *.mdw  *.prg  *.vbs  *.shtml
*.com  *.isp  *.mdz  *.reg  *.wsc  *.stm
*.cpl  *.js  *.msc  *.scf  *.wsf  *.xml"
          solution        : "Update the EDSP.

Open the Exchange Management Shell and enter the following command:

Add-AttachmentFilterEntry -Name <'*.FileExtension'> -Type FileName

Repeat the procedure for each undesirable attachment type."
          reference       : "800-53|SI-8(2),800-53r5|SI-8(2),CAT|II,CCI|CCI-001308,DISA_Benchmark|MS_Exchange_2013_Edge_STIG,GDPR|32.1.b,HIPAA|164.306(a)(1),ITSG-33|SI-8(2),QCSC-v1|3.2,QCSC-v1|8.2.1,Rule-ID|SV-234738r961161_rule,STIG-ID|EX13-EG-000200,STIG-Legacy|SV-84497,STIG-Legacy|V-69875,Vuln-ID|V-234738"
          see_also        : "https://dl.dod.cyber.mil/wp-content/uploads/stigs/zip/U_MS_Exchange_2013_Y24M07_STIG.zip"
          value_type      : POLICY_TEXT
          value_data      : "All policies compliant"
          powershell_args : "$exts = '*.ade','*.adp','*.app','*.asx','*.bas','*.bat','*.chm','*.cmd','*.com','*.cpl','*.crt','*.csh','*.dcr','*.dir','*.exe','*.fxp','*.hlp','*.hta','*.htc','*.htm','*.html','*.inf','*.ins','*.isp','*.js','*.jse','*.ksh','*.lnk','*.mda','*.mdb','*.mde','*.mht','*.mhtml','*.mdt','*.mdw','*.mdz','*.msc','*.msi','*.msp','*.mst','*.ops','*.pcd','*.pif','*.plg','*.prf','*.prg','*.reg','*.scf','*.scr','*.sct','*.shb','*.shs','*.shtm','*.shtml','*.spl','*.stm','*.swf','*.url','*.vb','*.vbe','*.vbs','*.wsc','*.wsf','*.wsh','*.xml','*.zip'; $settings = Get-AttachmentFilterEntry | Where {$_.Type -eq 'FileName'}; $settings | Format-List Type, Name, Identity; foreach ($entry in $settings) { $exts = $exts | Where-Object { $_ -ne $entry.Name }; } If ($exts) { 'Missing Attachment Filters:' + $exts } Else { 'All policies compliant' }"
          secure_string   : "@SECURE_STRING@"
          check_type      : CHECK_REGEX
        </custom_item>

        <custom_item>
          type            : AUDIT_EXCHANGE
          description     : "EX13-EG-000205 - The Exchange Spam Evaluation filter must be enabled."
          info            : "By performing filtering at the perimeter, up to 90 percent of spam, malware, and other undesirable messages may be eliminated from the transport message stream, preventing their entry into the Exchange environment. This significantly reduces the attack vector for inbound email-borne spam and malware.

